FBIS4-59105 "drnes091_j_94056" FBIS-NES-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Motorists Urged To Carry Vehicle Ownership Documents Motorists Urged To Carry Vehicle Ownership Documents JN1005064694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0430 GMT 10 May 94 JN1005064694 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Statement by the Interior Ministry; date and place not given--read by announcer] [Text] The Interior Ministry hereby announces to citizens throughout the governorates of the Republic of Yemen that they must abide by instructions to carry all documentation proving ownership of the cars they drive. The ministry stresses that no vehicle may be driven unless it meets pertinent legal requirements. The ministry agencies will carry out continuous inspection campaigns to seize violators. Warning against the gravity of ignoring these instructions, the ministry stresses that violators will be subject to stringent penalties. It hopes that all brother citizens will cooperate with and respond to these instructions.
